~ librarian_organization_quirk
Iris Bookwright: [#proud] I've revolutionized the Dewey Decimal System! \n \nEach book's placement corresponds to its optimal humidity, light exposure, and proximity to compatible texts. \n \n[#conspiratorial] Water conservation texts refuse to shelve next to fire ecology - sibling rivalry, you understand.
=> librarian_philosophy

~ librarian_philosophy
Iris Bookwright: [#philosophical] Libraries aren't just repositories of knowledge, my dear. \n \nThey're living ecosystems where ideas cross-pollinate like... well, like complex fungal networks!
- "That's beautiful" => librarian_beautiful_response
- "Do you ever have pest problems?" => librarian_pest_problems
- "Ask about something else" => librarian_main_menu
- "I should let you get back to work" => END

~ librarian_beautiful_response
Iris Bookwright: [#pleased] You understand! So few do. \n \n[#inspired] When two complementary texts are shelved nearby, sometimes new ideas literally sprout between them. \n \n[#mysterious] I've found hand-written notes that weren't there yesterday - the books talking to each other, perhaps?
if 0>1:
	do relationship_level += 1
