~ librarian_philosophy_continued
Iris Bookwright: [#thoughtful] The library breathes with its readers, you know. \n \n[#whimsical] Morning light activates the botanical texts, while evening awakens the astronomy collection. \n \n[#warm] Your appreciation suggests you might be a true bibliofungal enthusiast!
- "What else can you tell me?" => librarian_main_menu
- "I should go explore those sections" => END

~ librarian_pest_problems
Iris Bookwright: [#amused] Pest problems? In a way... \n \nThe silverfish have formed a symbiotic relationship with certain textbooks. \n \nThey only eat outdated information, you see. Very helpful for keeping our collection current. \n \nThough I do have to maintain the "No Eating Wikipedia Printouts" rule.
- "That's... convenient?" => librarian_pest_solution
- "Ask about something else" => librarian_main_menu
- "That's... a lot to think about" => END

~ librarian_pest_solution
Iris Bookwright: [#pragmatic] Quite! Though I had to negotiate boundaries with them. \n \n[#business-like] Outdated medical texts? Fair game. Rare first editions? Absolutely not. \n \nWe reached a dÃ©tente. They get the old almanacs, I get to keep my manuscripts.
=> librarian_main_menu

