- "These look ancient..." => librarian_ancient_books
- "Can I touch them?" => librarian_handling_books

~ librarian_spore_incident
Iris Bookwright: [#dramatic] Ah, you don't know? Sit down, this is quite the tale... \n \nIn 1894, a misguided mycologist tried to cultivate Amanita reading toadstools. \n \n[#ominous] He theorized they could absorb and share the knowledge from multiple books simultaneously.
Iris Bookwright: The resulting spore cloud covered three counties and caused temporary ecological enlightenment. \nFor one week, the local wildlife achieved perfect biodiversity balance. Briefly.
=> librarian_aftermath

~ librarian_aftermath
Iris Bookwright: [#thoughtful] These books survived by being sealed in a lead-lined vault.
Iris Bookwright: Some say you can still hear them whispering mycelial secrets if you listen closely at night.
Iris Bookwright: [#practical] I keep them here for "research purposes."
if 0 > 1:
	do QuestSystem.unlock_location("Hidden Archive")
- "What happened to the mycologist?" => librarian_mycologist_fate
- "Can we look at them?" => librarian_viewing_rare_books
